At Chateau Haut Brion, it has long been a practice for the proprietors to set aside, as a personal reserve, a number of bottles from each vintage year. These older wines

were served on special occasions to appreciative guests of the Chateau and were not on the general market of Bordeaux.

We proudly report that the Chateau has made available to the American public,

through us, in limited quantity, some of their rare old treasures, as well as oustanding examples of more recent vintage years.
